    • Method Detail

      • setTrackerTerminationMethod

        public void setTrackerTerminationMethod(java.lang.String value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Method via which the Migration Tracker will keep the JVM alive after the migration has completed in order to keep the UI alive long enough for all the data from OM to be transfered to the tracker. Defaults to "SLEEP" (30 seconds).
        Parameters:
        value - String method used to pause JVM execution for tracker purposes

      • setSleepMilliseconds

        public void setSleepMilliseconds(int value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. If the "SLEEP" option is provided for the tracker termination via the injected variable trackerTerminationMethod, this variable should be set to the amount of milliseconds the program should sleep for before terminating the JVM. Defaults to 30,000 (30 seconds).
        Parameters:
        value - int the number of milliseconds the program will pause for before terminating
